# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv. Other users of your project can then use it to install the same
#   version of Python.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS or architecture,
#   it might cause dependency resolution issues.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be included in version control, but it might be excluded.
# poetry.lock

